      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While many smart devices have motion and microphone capabilities, the idea that they are interpreting subtle changes in your breathing or tone to dictate temperature shifts is a massive leap in functionality. Most smart home integrations are designed for simple commands, not complex emotional analysis to control HVAC systems. It is more probable that a shared network fluctuation or a poorly calibrated sensor is reacting simultaneously to something else, like a nearby sound or a change in air pressure. You might want to isolate the devices to see if the behavior persists when they are on different Wi-Fi networks.",
