      "content": "i tried putting the thermostat on a separate guest network and its still doing it. it happens even when i'm alone in the house. it's just so specific... it's like they're waiting for me to reach a certain level of agitation. if they were actually sending data out, would it even show up in the standard logs? or could they be using something like side-channel communication to stay under the radar?",
